bibdata.title: Record with more than one call_number_browse or call_number_display should create an array of elements with the values

comments.body: the issue that I explained earlier in our checkin is: call number fields appear as one string: ``` "call_number_display": [ "01.XIII.19 JV6225 .R464 2001" ], "call_number_browse_s": [ "01.XIII.19 JV6225 .R464 2001" ], "call_number_locator_display": [ "01.XIII.19 JV6225 .R464 2001" the call number page will display with the call number as one string as: ```

with the fix call numbers will index as expected: (this is from my local index)
```
"call_number_display": [
"01.XIII.19",
"JV6225 .R464 2001"
],
"call_number_browse_s": [
"01.XIII.19",
"JV6225 .R464 2001"
],
"call_number_locator_display": [
"01.XIII.19",
"JV6225 .R464 2001"
```
![ezgif com-gif-maker (1)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9905193/127064242-3dcbda94-46d3-44a1-9415-3f12074470c1.gif)
